args: Please note that this story contains spoilers\nfor Chapter 14 of the main campaign.
Once every 99 years, the Rite of the Lambentree\nis conducted.
It is a sacred ritual of the Ilian Church where the\nAuspex offers her holy mana to the earth and sky.
Something on your mind, Elly?\nThat's quite the grimace you're rocking.
Hello, Notte. No, I was merely thinking...
If that's thinking, I'd hate to see fretting.\nC'mon, spill the beans to ol' Notte.
It regards the Rite of the Lambentree.
It is a ritual of the Church performed every\n99 years. In it, the Auspex offers her mana\nto a tree known as the Lambentree.
Said mana passes up through the tree and\ninto the heavens, returning to earth as holy\nrain said to bring prosperity to mankind.
Yeaaah, that sorta rings a bell. But wait,\nisn't the current Auspex...?
'Zactly. And since she's, uh, indisposed,\nI guess you've gotta cancel it.
No wonder you're bumming. Still, I'll bet\nthis isn't the first time this event hasn't\npanned out like everyone wanted.
Indeed, in times when no one possessing\nof the holy mana emerged to become\nAuspex, the rite was not held.
But in each case, an epoch-defining\ncalamity befell the land soon after.
Dude, this Lambentree has ZERO chill...
Yeah, this is a real dill of a pickle\nall right. Hmmmmmm...
I know who can take Zethia's place!
...And so you wish me to perform this rite\nin the stead of your Zethia?
We do. Will you grant us this boon?
I am willing to help, but...
C'mon, Zena! At least give it a shot!\nYou're seriously our only hope here.
Very well. I shall do what I can.
...So your condition is that I assist in your\ntraining? I certainly don't mind, but what\nmanner of training do you require?
Two powers inhabit my body; I wish to\ncultivate complete control over them.
One is your Auspex power, yeah?\nSo what's the other one?
Pray do not say a trace of the Other's\npower yet remains within you!
Alas, I had thought I'd completely\nexpelled it back then, but...
Aaah ha ha! What do you think you can do,\nbroken and powerless as you are?
But I have power enough left to send them\nfar from here!
You're talking about the fight at the\nBinding Ruins, right? When you saved us?
I am. In that struggle, I exhausted my\nmana and had to retreat, severing my path\nto this world in the process.
You know, I always forget that you're\njust a spiritual mana projection thingie.
Your body yet remains in your own world,\nclutching the Dawnshard in slumber.
The Dawnshard is incredible, but so, too,\nis the Auspex's power. To be able to exist\nbeyond your own world is truly miraculous.
I suppose it is. But as I am now,\nI both am the Auspex and am not.
There is only one way to perform the rite\nwith two conflicting powers within me:
I must learn to suppress the Other's power\nentirely while releasing my mana in full.
So you have to maintain absolute control\nover two totally opposite energies at the\nsame time? Yikes, dude. YIKES.
Is turning one off completely while the\nother's going full blast even possible?
I shall have to attempt it and see.\nI will suppress the Other now...
So this is the mana of the Auspex...
Ooo, it's all sparkly and warm!\nIt's totally different from normal magic!
I am sorry. The process was going well\nat first, but then...
Holy twerks, that was amazing—you even\ngot a new outfit! ...Actually, hang on.\nWHY did you get a new outfit, exactly?
My body and clothing both are\ncomprised entirely of mana.
I was intentionally suppressing the\nOther's power and releasing holy mana,\nso that must have affected my outfit.
Spiritual mana projections are a\ncurious thing indeed.
What do you think, Zena?\nWill you be able to conduct the rite?
It will require some time,\nbut I shall do my best.
And the strain isn't too great?
Er, it is nothing. Now if you will excuse\nme, I am drained and need to rest.
She seemed a little hesitant when we\nfirst asked her, but got pretty fired up\nby the end there!
But do you think she'll be all right?\nIt seemed pretty rough on her.
We can do naught but trust in her;\nZena is the only one who can spare\nthis world from utter calamity.
(I must succeed—for my own salvation\nas much as theirs.)
